-- 
Mozambique Power Line to Cost $2 Billion, Noticias Reports

-- B y   F r e d   K a t e r e r e
-- 
2011-06-09T12:03:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-09/mozambique-power-line-to-cost-2-billion-noticias-reports.html
The construction of a transmission
line from the 3,000-megawatt Cahora Bassa hydroelectric dam in
northwestern  Mozambique  to the capital, Maputo, will cost $2
billion, Noticias said, citing Energy Minister Salvador Namburete.  The line will be in addition to cables that carry
electricity to the neighboring nations of  South Africa  and
Zimbabwe, the Maputo-based newspaper said.  Finance for building the line, which will start in August,
will come from the World Bank, European Development Bank,
African Development Bank, the governments of Norway and France
and Portuguese companies, Namburete told the Noticias.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Katerere in Maputo at 
 fkaterere@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 